        "id": "def-server.getSpaceNPRE",
        "type": "Function",
        "tags": [
          "throws"
        ],
        "label": "getSpaceNPRE",
        "description": [
          "\nGet the NPRE for a given space ID or a request carrying a URL.\n\nWhen a request object is provided, the space is taken from a URL pathname via\n{@link getSpaceIdFromPath}. If the request has a `rewrittenUrl` (set by core\nwhen the first `onPreRouting` handler returns `rewriteUrl`), that URL is\nused instead of `url`. This matches HTTP requests after the Spaces plugin\nstrips `/s/:spaceId` from `request.url` during pre-routing: the original\nbrowser path (including the space segment) remains on `rewrittenUrl`.\n\n**Server base path**: {@link getSpaceIdFromPath} is called with the pathname\nonly; a non-root `server.basePath` is not stripped here. CPS is only\navailable on Serverless, where custom base paths are not used, so this\nlimitation is not a practical concern for CPS.\n"
        ],
        "signature": [
          "(spaceIdOrRequest: string | ",
          "ScopeableUrlRequest",
          ") => string"
        ],
